onsistently supports the structure **3,5-bis(4-fluorophenyl)-1,2,4-thiadiazole**. The asymmetry of the 1,2,4-thiadiazole core explains the two distinct environments for the 4-fluorophenyl rings.\n\nFINAL_RESULT:\n  UUID: 64f0986f-605f-4b9a-a7e1-198f5237babe\n  PREDICTED_SMILES: Fc1ccc(cc1)c2nc(ns2)c3ccc(F)cc3\n  CONFIDENCE: 0.98\n  REASON_BRIEF: The formula C14H8F2N2S and 1H NMR suggest two 4-fluorophenyl rings attached to a central core. 13C NMR shows 10 signals indicating asymmetry, and the diagnostic shifts at 187.0 ppm (C-5) and 172.8 ppm (C-3) confirm the core as 1,2,4-thiadiazole.",
